Class CompositeIDMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.server.master.identity.CompositeIDMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LocalIdentityMapper, org.springframework.beans.factory.Aware, org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware

    public class CompositeIDMapper
extends Object
implements LocalIdentityMapper, org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware
    An identity mapper that composes the results from other mappers, using the identity mappers in order until one can provide a non-null answer.
    Author:
    Donal Fellows.

      • getUsernameForPrincipal

        public String getUsernameForPrincipal(UsernamePrincipal user)
        Description copied from interface: LocalIdentityMapper
        Given a user's identity, get the local identity to use for executing their workflows. Note that it is assumed that there will never be a failure from this interface; it is not a security policy decision or enforcement point.
        Specified by:
        getUsernameForPrincipal in interface LocalIdentityMapper
        Parameters:
        user - An identity token.
        Returns:
        A user name, which must be defined in the context that workflows will be running in.
